title: Drawing, Design for Six-Legged Rectangular Dining Table, 1900–05
title_raw: Design for Six-Legged Rectangular Dining Table
medium: Pen and black ink, graphite on thin cream paper
inscribed: Inscribed in pen and black ink, bottom right: Dining Table; in graphite, upper right of image: 4.' 3" sq.-
creditline: Gift of The Lake St. Louis Historical Society
description: Rectangular table top with dividing stretcher running across center, raised on 6 [5  shown] plain, straight, tapering legs on cup casters; legs clustered in pairs, one pair on either side and one pair center.

participants.person_name: The Lake St. Louis Historical Society
